1 requests access. An unserved area also includes an area that was previously
2 served but has become unserved due to damage or destruction by a natural
3 disaster. A pole or underground installation shall be presumed to be located in
4 an unserved area if the pole is located in an area that is the subject of a federal
5 or State grant to deploy broadband service, the conditions of which limit the
6 availability of a grant to unserved areas.areas or, in the case of a damaged or
7 destroyed facility, was in such an area when the facility was originally
8 constructed.
9 (10) Utility. – As defined by 47 U.S.C. § 224.
10 …."
11 SECTION 3.2. This Part is effective when it becomes law. Funds encumbered for
12 expenses incurred under this Part as of June 1, 2021, prior to the effective date of this Part shall
13 remain eligible for reimbursement.
14
15 PART IV. FUNDING FLEXIBILITY
16 SECTION 4.1. Section 38.15 of S.L. 2021-180, as enacted by Section 16.1(a) of
17 S.L. 2022-6, reads as rewritten:
18 "SECTION 38.15. Except as otherwise provided, provided and after the intent of the original
19 appropriation has been satisfied to the extent practicable, the Department of Information
20 Technology shall have flexibility to transfer funding between the programs outlined in Section
21 38.4, Section 38.5, and Section 38.6 38.6, and Sections 38.10(b) through (k) of this act, so long
22 as the total allocations for the programs remain the same.act."
23
24 PART V. LIFELINE SERVICE PROVIDERS
25 SECTION 5.1. Article 3 of Chapter 62 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
26 a new section to read:
27 "§ 62-30.1. Designating telecommunications carriers; rules.
28 (a) Notwithstanding G.S. 62-3(23)j. or G.S. 62-30, the Utilities Commission may, solely
29 upon petition of any provider or reseller of mobile radio communications service, designate the
30 petitioning provider or reseller of mobile radio communications service as an eligible
31 telecommunications carrier pursuant to 47 C.F.R. § 54.201 for purposes of providing Lifeline
32 service. The Commission may adopt rules to effectuate the purposes of this section.
33 (b) Nothing in this section shall confer upon the Utilities Commission any regulatory
34 jurisdiction over providers or resellers of mobile radio communications service that have been
35 previously designated as eligible telecommunications carriers for purposes of providing Lifeline
36 service prior to the enactment of this section."
37
38 PART VI. EFFECTIVE DATE
39 SECTION 6.1. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
40 law.
